** About the company   
** Palladium is a global leader in the design, development, and delivery of Positive Impact - the intentional creation of enduring social and economic value. With a team of more than 2,500 employees operating in 90-plus countries and a global network of more than 35,000 technical experts, Palladium has improved - and is committed to continuing to improve - economies, societies, and most importantly, people's lives.   
  
** About the Project **   
The Humanitarian Logistics Capability (HLC) contract is a partnership between
The Palladium Group and the Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade (DFAT).
The HLC program itself supports the Australian Government's international
disaster relief efforts through the provision of logistical support, disaster
relief procurement, and timely technical advice.  
  
** About the role **   
As a short-term contractual role, the HLC is looking to recruit a Platform
Developer who is highly experienced in either Oracle APEX or Microsoft Power
Apps. The role will drive forward a time-sensitive project for the design,
development, and implementation of a new Management Information System. This
role is based in Pinkenba, Brisbane.  
  
** The primary responsibilities: **   
Develop a Management Information System on Oracle APEX or Microsoft Power
Apps. Ensure platform meets project requirements.  
Work closely with Business Analyst and HLC and DFAT stakeholders to gather and
understand project-specific requirements.  
Design and implement scalable solutions using Oracle APEX or Microsoft Power
Apps, SQL, and PL/SQL.  
Troubleshoot and resolve issues promptly to meet project deadlines.  
Collaborate with the Business Analyst and project manager to ensure project
success.  
Provide regular updates on project progress and raise any potential risks or
roadblocks.  
  
** About You: **   
Proven experience building Oracle APEX or Microsoft Power Apps platforms, with
a successful track record of project delivery.  
In-depth knowledge of either Oracle APEX or Microsoft Power Apps, SQL, and
PL/SQL development.  
Experience building client-facing Dashboards that provide users with a
consolidated view of operations.  
Strong understanding of database design principles and optimization
techniques.  
Experience with version control systems and collaborative development tools.  
Git / Azure DevOps / Subversion (SVN) / Oracle APEX Versioning / Microsoft
Power Platform Version Control  
Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to work in a fast-paced
environment.  
Effective communication skills and the ability to work collaboratively in a
team.  
Oracle APEX or Microsoft Power Apps certifications are a plus.  
  
Note: Individuals or businesses may apply. Short-listed candidates will be
provided with the design concept and requested to present their approach
during interview.  
  
** Benefits: **   
Flexible working arrangements.  
Great team culture with social activities and events and true comradery.  
Work with a passionate team creating real difference in people's lives.  
Be at the forefront of Australia's response to international disasters and
COVID crises in the Indo-Pacific region.  
This is a great opportunity to work for a purpose and change the lives of
others for the better.  
  
